.\" -*- nroff -*-
.TH ARCCLIENT.XML 5 "@DATE@" "NorduGrid ARC @VERSION@" "NorduGrid Users Manual"

.SH NAME

arcclient.xml \- ARC user configuration

.SH DESCRIPTION

User configuration for NorduGrid ARC.

.SH SYNOPSIS

.B ${ARC_LOCATION}/etc/arcclient.xml

.B /etc/arcclient.xml

.B ~/.arc/client.xml

.SH EXTENDED DESCRIPTION

The ARC user configuration consists of two files. One system wide
configuration in
.B ${ARC_LOCATION}/etc/arcclient.xml
or
.BR /etc/arcclient.xml ,
and one per-user configuration file in
.BR ~/.arc/client.xml .
Most commands take a
.B --conffile
option to use a custom location for the per-user configuration file.

The configuration files are written in XML. Any XML tag present in the
per-user configuration file overrides all tags with the same name in
the system wide configuration file.

The following things can be configured in the user configuration file:

.B DefaultServices

This tag identifies the default starting points if no
.B --index
or
.B --cluster
options are give on the command line for
.B arcsub
and
.BR arcstat .

.IR Example :

.ft CR
.nf
<ArcConfig>
  <DefaultServices>
    <URL Flavour="ARC0" ServiceType="index">ldap://index1.nordugrid.org:2135/Mds-Vo-name=NorduGrid,o=grid</URL>
    <URL Flavour="ARC0" ServiceType="index">ldap://index2.nordugrid.org:2135/Mds-Vo-name=NorduGrid,o=grid</URL>
    <URL Flavour="ARC0" ServiceType="index">ldap://index3.nordugrid.org:2135/Mds-Vo-name=NorduGrid,o=grid</URL>
    <URL Flavour="ARC0" ServiceType="index">ldap://index4.nordugrid.org:2135/Mds-Vo-name=NorduGrid,o=grid</URL>
    <URL Flavour="ARC1" ServiceType="computing">https://knowarc1.grid.niif.hu:60000/arex</URL>
    <URL Flavour="CREAM" ServiceType="index">ldap://cream.grid.upjs.sk:2170/o=Grid</URL>
  </DefaultServices>
</ArcConfig>
.fi
.ft R


.B Alias

This tag can be used to create a shorthand notation for the arguents to the
.B --cluster
and
.B --index
options to the ARC command line tools. The definitions can be used recursively
as in the last example.

.IR Example :

.ft CR
.nf
<ArcConfig>
  <Alias name="myfavorite1">
    <URL Flavour="ARC0" ServiceType="computing">ldap://grid.tsl.uu.se:2135/nordugrid-cluster-name=grid.tsl.uu.se,Mds-Vo-name=local,o=grid</URL>
  </Alias>
  <Alias name="myfavorite2">
    <URL Flavour="ARC1" ServiceType="computing">https://knowarc1.grid.niif.hu:60000/arex</URL>
  </Alias>
  <Alias name="myfavorite3">
    <URL Flavour="CREAM" ServiceType="computing">ldap://cream.grid.upjs.sk:2170/Mds-Vo-name=knowarc-cream,o=grid</URL>
  </Alias>
  <Alias name="myfavorites">
    <Alias>myfavorite1</Alias>
    <Alias>myfavorite2</Alias>
    <Alias>myfavorite3</Alias>
  </Alias>
</ArcConfig>
.fi
.ft R

.B Debug

This tag defines the default debug level.

.IR Example :

.ft CR
.nf
<ArcConfig>
  <Debug>INFO</Debug>
</ArcConfig>
.fi
.ft R

.B ProxyPath, CertificatePath, KeyPath, CACertificatesDir

These tags can be used to override the location of certificates if the
default locations are not used.

.IR Example :

.ft CR
.nf
<ArcConfig>
  <ProxyPath>/tmp/my-proxy</ProxyPath>
  <CertificatePath>/home/username/cert.pem</CertificatePath>
  <KeyPath>/home/username/key.pem</KeyPath>
  <CACertificatesDir>/home/username/certificates</CACertificatesDir>
</ArcConfig>
.fi
.ft R

